@tablet

@obverse

1. [...] gaš-ru bu-kur₂ {d}EN#.[LIL₂]
#tr.en: Mighty [. . .], son of En[lil],

2. [... git₂]-ma#-lum e-til!(LIT)-ti e₂-šar₂-[ra]
#tr.en: [. . . per]fect one, progeny of Esha[ra],

3. [...] lit#-bu-šu₂ ma-lu-u hur#-ba#-[šu₂]
#tr.en: [. . .] clothed [. . .], filled with terr[or],

4. [...] la# im-mah-ha-ru qa-bal#-[šu₂]
#tr.en: [. . . whose] onslaught cannot be opposed,

5. šu-pu-u man#-[za]-za#-šu₂ DINGIR-MEŠ GAL-MEŠ
#tr.en: Whose (celestial) po[si]tion is resplendent (among) the great gods,

6. ina e₂-kur E₂ ta#-ši#-la#-a-ti ša₂-qa-a re-ša₂-ka#
#tr.en: In Ekur, the house of celebrations, your head is high.

7. id#-din-ka-ma {d}[EN.LIL₂] AD-ka#
#tr.en: [Enlil], your father, gave you,

8. te#-rit kul-lat DINGIR-MEŠ qa-tuk#-ka# DIB{+hat#}
#tr.en: Executive power over all the gods; it is held in your hand.

9. [ta]-da-an di-in te-ne#-še-e-te
#tr.en: [You] pass judgment upon the people.

10. [tuš]-te-šir la šu-šu-ru e-ka-a e-ku#-[ti]
#tr.en: You secure justice for the misguided, the orphaned boy and girl.

11. ta#-ṣa-bat ŠU en-ši la li-ʾ-a tu-x-[x-x]
#tr.en: You take the hand of the powerless, you [. . .] the helpless.

12. ša₂#? ana#? a-ra-le-e šu-ru-du pa-gar-šu₂ GUR{+ra?#}
#tr.en: You return the body (lit. his body) of the one being made to descend into the netherworld.

13. ša₂# ar₂-nu i-šu-u ta-paṭ-ṭar [...]
#tr.en: You forgive [. . .] of the one who has incurred guilt.

14. ša₂# DINGIR#-šu₂# {d}IŠ₈.TAR₂-<šu₂> zi-nu-u₂# [...]
#tr.en: [. . .] to the one whose (personal) god (and personal) goddess are angry [. . . ].

15. {d#}MAŠ# a#-ša₂#-red# DINGIR#-MEŠ# qu#-ra#-du# at#-[ta]
#tr.en: O Ninurta, foremost of the gods, yo[u] (are) the hero.

16. a-na-ku {I}3(u)-MAN-GAR DUMU# DINGIR-šu₂
#tr.en: I (am) Sîn-šar-iškun, son of his god,

17. ša₂# DINGIR#-šu₂ AN.ŠAR₂ {d#}IŠ₈#.TAR₂#-šu₂ {d}aš₂-šur-i-tu₂
#tr.en: whose (personal) god (is) Ashur, (and) whose (personal) goddess (is) Ashuritu.

18. ar-kus-ka rik#-sa ZI₃.EŠA as₂-ruq#-[ka]
#tr.en: I have set up a ritual arrangement for you. I have str[ewn] flour for [you].
#note: Other witnesses include one more line before the following one in this MS.

19. BAL-ka du-uš#-šu₂-pa ši-[kar] aš-na#-[an]
#tr.en: I have libated sweet ale for you, be[er] made from (lit. of) grai[n].

20. KI-ka li-iz-ziz-zu DINGIR#-[MEŠ šu]-ut# {d}[EN.LIL₂]
#tr.en: May the god[s of the (Path of) Enlil] stand with you.

21. KI-ka li-iz#-ziz#-zu# [...] e₂-[kur]
#tr.en: May the gods, [. . .] of Ekur, stand with you.

22. x x [...] x [...]
#tr.en: [. . .]

