2. <<TAB>> zik-ri li-ṭib UGU-ka#
#tr.en: May my speech please you.

3. si-lim KI ia-a-a-te pa-lih-[ka]
#tr.en: Be at peace with me, the one who fears [you].

4. pa-ni-ka a-ta-mar lu-še-ra a-[na-ku]
#tr.en: I have seen your face. May I [indeed] prosper.

5. mu-up-pal-sa-ta ki-niš nap-lis-a-ni#
#tr.en: You are favorably disposed; look upon me with due favor.

6. ar₂-ni pu-ṭur še-er-ti pu-šur#
#tr.en: Remove my guilt; forgive my offence.

7. šu-ti-iq gil-la-ti-ma hi-ṭi-te [...]
#tr.en: Make my sin pass by; [. . .] (my) negligence.

8. DINGIR-MU {d}IŠ₈.TAR₂-MU li-ša₂-qi₂-ru-ni#-[ma?]
#tr.en: May my (personal) god (and personal) goddess respect me;

9. liq-bu-u SIG₅{+tim#}
#tr.en: May they intercede (for me),

10. nar-bi-ka lu-ša₂-pi!(ka) da₃-li₂-li₂-ka lud#-[lul]
#tr.en: That I may proclaim your greatness (and) res[ound] your praises.

